"operating systems are not very smart about managing this, and will allow "
"large amounts of dirty data to accumulate then decide to flush it all at "
"once, leading to long delays for new I/O requests. This change attempts to "
"alleviate this problem by explicitly requesting data flushes after a "
"configurable interval."
msgstr ""

